burnt\n|-\n|''[[French ship Juste (1726)|Juste]]''\n|70\n|{{Interlanguage link multi|Fran\u00e7ois de Saint-Allouarn|fr}}\n|630\n|Wrecked in the Loire\n|-\n|''Inflexible''\n|64\n|Tancrede\n|540\n|Lost at the entrance to the Vilaine\n|-\n|''Sphinx''\n|64\n|Goyon\n|450\n|Escaped to the Vilaine, blockaded there until April, 1762{{sfn|Troude|1867|p=}}\n|-\n|''Bizarre''\n|64\n|[[Jules, Prince of Gu\u00e9m\u00e9n\u00e9|Prince de Montbazon]]\n|450\n|Escaped to Rochefort\n|-\n|'''''Frigates and corvettes'''''\n|-\n|''H\u00e9b\u00e9''\n|40\n|\n|300\n|Returned to Brest\n|-\n|''Aigrette''\n|36\n|\n|\n|Escaped to the Vilaine\n|-\n|''[[French ship Vestale (1756)|Vestale]]''\n|34\n|\n|254\n|Escaped to the Vilaine\n|-\n|''Calypso''\n|16\n|{{Interlanguage link multi|Paul Alexandre du Bois-Berthelot|fr}}\n|\n|Escaped to the Vilaine\n|-\n|''Prince Noir''\n|6\n|{{Interlanguage link multi|Pierre-Joseph Kergariou de Roscouet|fr}}\n|\n|Escaped to the Vilaine\n|-\n|'''''Other'''''\n|-\n|''Vengeance''\n|?\n|\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n===Britain===\n\n[[File:HMS Royal George, 1759 Gravur, Walzahn.jpg|thumb|HMS ''Royal George'', Hawke's flagship at Quiberon Bay \u2013 a replica of walrus ivory]]\nOrder of Battle:{{sfn|Troude|1867|p=385}}\n{|\n|'''Name'''\n|'''Guns'''\n|'''Commander'''\n|'''Men'''\n|'''Notes'''\n|-\n|''[[HMS Royal George (1756)|Royal George]]''\n|100\n|[[John Campbell (Royal Navy officer)|John Campbell]]\n|880\n|Flagship of [[Edward Hawke|Sir Edward Hawke]]\n|-\n|''[[HMS Union (1756)|Union]]''\n|90\n|Thomas Evans\n|770\n|Flagship of [[Charles Hardy|Sir Charles Hardy]]\n|-\n|''[[HMS Vanguard (1678)|Duke]]''\n|80\n|[[Samuel Graves]]\n|800\n|\n|-\n|''[[HMS Namur (1756)|Namur]]''\n|90\n|[[Matthew Buckle]]\n|780\n|\n|-\n|''[[HMS Mars (1759)|Mars]]''\n|74\n|Commodore [[James Young (1717\u20131789)|James Young]]\n|600\n|\n|-\n|''[[HMS Warspite (1758)|Warspite]]''\n|74\n|Sir John Bentley\n|600\n|\n|-\n|''[[HMS Hercules (1759)|Hercules]]''\n|74\n|William Fortescue\n|600\n|\n|-\n|''[[HMS Neptune (