{"title_page": "Okta (identity management)", "text_new": "{{Advert|date=December 2018}} \n{{Infobox company\n| name = Okta, Inc.\n| logo = Okta logo.svg\n| caption = \n| trading_name = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above -->\n| native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->\n| romanized = \n| former type = \n| type = Public\n| traded_as = {{NASDAQ|OKTA}}<br>[[Russell 1000 Index]] component\n| industry = [[Software Industry|Software]]\n| genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies -->\n| fate = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| foundation = January 2009; 11 years ago \n| founder = Todd McKinnon, Frederic Kerrest\n| defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| location_city = [[San Francisco, California]]\n| location_country = \n| locations = <!-- Number of locations, stores, offices, etc. -->\n| area_served = Worldwide\n| key_people = Todd McKinnon, CEO<br />Frederic Kerrest, COO\n| products = Single Sign-On\n| production = \n| services = \n| revenue = \n| operating_income = \n| net_income = \n| aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies -->\n| assets = \n| equity = \n| owner = \n| num_employees = \n| parent = \n| divisions = \n| subsid = \n| homepage = {{URL|www.okta.com}}\n| footnotes = \n| intl = \n| bodystyle = \n}}\n'''Okta, Inc.''' is a publicly traded [[identity and access management]] company based in San Francisco.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.barrons.com/articles/okta-ceo-is-feeling-optimistic-looks-like-investors-are-too-1512597027|title=Okta CEO Is Feeling Optimistic. Looks Like Investors Are Too|last=Rivas|first=Teresa|date=December 6, 2017|work=Barron's|access-date=April 8, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> It provides cloud software that helps companies manage and secure user authentication into modern applications, and for developers to build identity controls into applications, website web services and devices.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/adrianbridgwater/2018/05/23/okta-insists-identity-goes-beyond-passwords/|title=Okta Insists Identity 'Goes Beyond' Passwords|last=Bridgwater|first=Adrian|date=May 23, 2018|work=Forbes|access-date=March 6, 2019|language=en-US}}</ref>  It was founded in 2009 and had its [[initial public offering]] in 2017, being valued at over $6 billion.\n\n== Services ==\nOkta sells six services, including a single sign-on solution that allows users to log into a variety of systems using one centralized process. For example, the company claims the ability to log into [[Gmail]], [[Workday, Inc.|Workday]], [[Salesforce.com|Salesforce]] and [[Slack (software)|Slack]] with one login.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.barrons.com/articles/okta-ceo-we-exist-because-its-a-heterogenous-world-1516661447|title=Okta CEO: \u2018We Exist Because It\u2019s a Heterogenous World\u2019|last=Ray|first=Tiernan|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.barrons.com/articles/okta-as-big-a-deal-as-oracle-someday-1497048753|title=Okta: A Bigger Deal Than Oracle Someday?|last=Ray|first=Tiernan|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en-US}}</ref> It also offers [[Application programming interface|API]] authentication services.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://fortune.com/2017/04/07/okta-ipo-todd-mckinnon/|title=Okta Wants To Go Big And Go It Alone in Enterprise Software|work=Fortune|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOkta's services are built on top of the [[Amazon Web Services]] cloud.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fortune.com/2017/03/13/okta-cybersecurity-public/|title=This Enterprise Software Unicorn Just Filed to Go Public|work=Fortune|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2019, Okta's CEO announced that the company has over 100 million registered users.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/01/24/okta-ceo-we-now-have-over-100-million-registered-users.html|title=Okta CEO: We now have over 100 million registered users|last=Gurdus|first=Elizabeth|date=2019-01-24|website=www.cnbc.com|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nOkta was founded in 2009. Current Okta CEO and co-founder Todd McKinnon previously served as the senior vice president of engineering at Salesforce. Prior to Salesforce, he held various roles at [[PeopleSoft]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Okta CEO McKinnon on the Tech IPO Landscape and Data Security|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2018-03-27/okta-ceo-mckinnon-on-the-tech-ipo-landscape-and-data-security-video|language=en|accessdate=2018-04-08}}</ref> Okta COO Frederic Kerrest is the other co-founder, also previously of Salesforce.\n\nIn 2015 the company raised $75 million in venture capital from [[Andreessen Horowitz]], [[Greylock Partners]] and [[Sequoia Capital]] at a valuation of $1.2 billion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2015/09/08/okta-raises-75-million-boosting-valuation-to-nearly-1-2-billion/|title=Okta Raises $75 Million, Boosting Valuation to Nearly $1.2 Billion|last=Ovide|first=Shira|date=2015-09-08|website=WSJ|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref> It previously raised $150 million across earlier funding rounds.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/okta|title=Okta {{!}} Crunchbase|website=Crunchbase|language=en|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 its initial public offering raised an additional $187 million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2017/04/07/okta-shares-debut.html|title=Okta shares soar nearly 39 percent in first day of trading|website=www.bizjournals.com|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref> It traded up on its first day.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/04/07/okta-ipo-opening-stock-price.html|title=Okta skyrockets more than 38% after IPO|last=Balakrishnan|first=Anita|date=2017-04-07|work=CNBC|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref> At the time of its IPO, Sequoia Capital was the biggest shareholder, with a 21.2 percent stake.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/sanfrancisco/news/2017/04/07/okta-shares-debut.html|title=Okta shares soar nearly 39 percent in first day of trading|website=www.bizjournals.com|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref>\n\nThe company is headquartered in [[San Francisco]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/profiles/companies/OKTA:US-okta-inc|title=Okta Inc: Company Profile|website=Bloomberg|language=en|access-date=2018-04-08}}</ref> It also has offices in  [[San Jose, California|San Jose]], [[Bellevue, Washington|Bellevue]], [[Toronto]], [[Washington, D.C.|Washington D.C.]], [[London]], [[Amsterdam]], [[Sydney]],  [[Paris]] and [[Stockholm]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.okta.com/contact/|title=Get in Touch - Contact Information|website=okta|language=en|access-date=2018-04-12}}</ref>\n\nOkta primarily targets enterprise businesses. Current customers include JetBlue, Nordstrom, MGM Resorts International and the U.S. Department of Justice.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://venturebeat.com/2018/03/07/okta-identity-cloud-securely-connects-jetblue-to-its-customers/|title=Okta Identity Cloud Securely Connects JetBlue to its Customers|date=2018-03-07|work=Venturebeat|access-date=2019-06-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIt runs an annual \u201cOktane\u201d user conference, which recently featured former President Barack Obama as a keynote speaker.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/adrianbridgwater/2018/04/04/inside-privacy-okta-ceo-takes-hardcore-line-on-identity-management/2/|title=Inside Privacy: Okta CEO Takes Hardcore Line On Identity Management|last=Bridgwater|first=Adrian|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/oktane-18-barack-obama-todd-mckinnon-2018-5|title=I followed the CEO of $6 billion Okta around and learned the secrets of a tech conference that landed President Obama as a speaker|last=Bort|first=Julie|work=BusinessInsider|access-date=2019-06-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/business/article/Barack-Obama-is-speaking-at-a-tech-conference-12928567.php|title=Barack Obama is speaking at a tech conference, but not one you\u2019d expect|last=Thadani|first=Trisha|work=SFChronicle|access-date=2019-06-26|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Competitors ==\n\n* IBM Security\n*Auth0\n* Salesforce Identity \n* CA Technologies\n* Ping Identity\n* SailPoint\n*[[Microsoft Azure]] Active Directory\n*[[AWS]] Cognito\n* Centrify\n* Idaptive \n*MicroFocus (NetIQ) \n*[[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]] Enterprise SSO\n*[[OneLogin]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.inc.com/sonya-mann/okta-ipo-competitors.html|title=Okta's $187 Million Tech IPO Isn't Scaring Off Rivals|date=2017-04-07|work=Inc.com|access-date=2018-04-08|language=en}}</ref>\n*Tools4ever HelloID\n*miniOrange\n*LoginRadius\n*[[ForgeRock]]\n*FusionAuth\n*JumpCloud\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Federated identity]]\n[[Category:Identity management systems]]\n[[Category:Cloud applications]]\n[[Category:Identity management]]\n[[Category:Access control software]]\n[[Category:Password authentication]]\n[[Category:Software companies based in the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2009]]\n[[Category:2017 initial public offerings]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on NASDAQ]]\n[[Category:Software companies of the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Advert|date=December 2018}} \n{{Infobox company\n| name = Okta, Inc.\n| logo = Okta logo.svg\n| caption = \n| trading_name = <!-- d/b/a/, doing business as - if different from legal name above -->\n| native_name = <!-- Company's name in home country language -->\n| native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-2 code, e.g. \"fr\" for French. If there is more than one native name, in different languages, enter those names using {{tl|lang}}, instead. -->