} [[Shaun Murphy]] (5)|7 |{{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Ronnie O'Sullivan]] (12)'''}}|'''13'''\n<!--Match4 -->\n|21 & 22 April|{{flagicon|CHN}} [[Liang Wenbo]] (13)|12 |{{flagicon|CHN}} '''[[Ding Junhui]] (4)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match5 -->\n|20 & 21 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Stuart Bingham]] (3)|10 |{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Kyren Wilson]] (14)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match6 -->\n|21 & 22 April|{{flagicon|NIR}} [[Mark Allen (snooker player)|Mark Allen]] (11)|9 |{{flagicon|SCO}} '''[[John Higgins]] (6)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match7 -->\n|23 & 24 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Barry Hawkins]] (7)'''|'''13''' |{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Graeme Dott]]|6\n<!--Match8 -->\n|22 & 23 April|{{flagicon|SCO}} '''[[Stephen Maguire]]'''|'''13''' |{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Rory McLeod (snooker player)|Rory McLeod]]|3\n<!-- QUARTER-FINALS -->\n<!--Match1 -->\n|25 & 26 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Mark Selby]] (1)'''|'''13''' |{{flagicon|HKG}} [[Marco Fu]] (8)|3\n<!--Match2 -->\n|25 & 26 April|{{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Ronnie O'Sullivan]] (12)}}|10 |{{flagicon|CHN}} '''[[Ding Junhui]] (4)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match3 -->\n|25 & 26 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Kyren Wilson]] (14)|6 |{{flagicon|SCO}} '''[[John Higgins]] (6)'''|'''13'''\n<!--Match4 -->\n|25 & 26 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Barry Hawkins]] (7)'''|'''13''' |{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Stephen Maguire]]|9\n<!-- SEMI-FINALS -->\n<!--Match1 -->\n|27, 28 & 29 April|{{flagicon|ENG}} '''[[Mark Selby]] (1)'''|'''17''' |{{nowrap|{{flagicon|CHN}} [[Ding Junhui]] (4)}}|15\n<!--Match2 -->\n|27, 28 & 29 April|{{flagicon|SCO}} '''[[John Higgins]] (6)'''|'''17''' |{{nowrap|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Barry Hawkins]] (7)}}|8\n<!-- FINAL -->\n|(Best of 35 frames) [[Crucible Theatre]], [[Sheffield]], 30 April & 1 May. Referee: {{flagicon|NED}} [[Jan Verhaas]]\n| '''[[Mark Selby]] (1)'''<br/>{{ENG}}\n| '''18'''\u201315\n| [[John Higgins]] (6)<br/>{{SCO}}\n| {{nowrap|'''76'''\u201334 ('''76'''),}} {{nowrap|7\u201350,}} {{nowrap|'''121'''\u20138 ('''62''', '''58'''),}} {{nowrap|0\u2013141 (141),}} {{nowrap|40\u201399 (63),}} {{nowrap|1\u2013126 (95),}} {{nowrap|54\u201359 (58),}} {{nowrap|33\u201368}}\n| Session 1<br/> {{nowrap|Session score: (2\u2013'''6'''), Match score: 2\u2013'''6'''}}\n| {{nowrap|76\u201334 (76),}} {{nowrap|7\u2013'''50''',}} {{nowrap|121\u20138 (62, 58),}} {{nowrap|0\u2013'''141''' ('''141'''),}} {{nowrap|40\u2013'''99''' ('''63'''),}} {{nowrap|1\u2013'''126''' ('''95'''),}} {{nowrap|54\u2013'''59''' ('''58'''),}} {{nowrap|33\u2013'''68'''}}\n| {{nowrap|'''86'''\u20130 ('''86'''),}} {{nowrap|8\u201360,}} {{nowrap|44\u201374,}} {{nowrap|'''69'''\u201322,}} {{nowrap|1\u201368,}} {{nowrap|0\u201376 (76),}} {{nowrap|'''81'''\u20139 ('''81'''),}} {{nowrap|'''121'''\u201312 ('''121'''),}} {{nowrap|'''96'''\u201317}}\n| Session 2<br/> {{nowrap|Session score: ('''5'''\u20134),  Match score: 7\u2013'''10'''}}\n| {{nowrap|86\u20130 (86),}} {{nowrap|8\u2013'''60''',}} {{nowrap|44\u2013'''74''',}} {{nowrap|69\u201322, 1\u2013'''68''',}} {{nowrap|0\u2013'''76''' ('''76'''),}} {{nowrap|81\u20139 (81),}} {{nowrap|121\u201312 (121),}} {{nowrap|96\u201317}}\n| {{nowrap|'''76'''\u20131,}} {{nowrap|'''53'''\u20132,}} {{nowrap|29\u2013107 (78),}} {{nowrap|'''63'''\u201340,}} {{nowrap|'''68'''\u201319 ('''67'''),}} {{nowrap|'''82'''\u20130 ('''58'''),}} {{nowrap|'''72'''\u20130 ('''72''')}}\n| Session 3<br/> {{nowrap|Session score: ('''6'''\u20131), Match score '''13'''\u201311}}\n| {{nowrap|76\u20131,}} {{nowrap|53\u20132,}} {{nowrap|29\u2013'''107''' ('''78'''),}} {{nowrap|63\u201340,}} {{nowrap|68\u201319 (67),}} {{nowrap|82\u20130 (58),}} {{nowrap|72\u20130 (72)}}\n| {{nowrap|'''72'''\u201322,}} {{nowrap|36\u201374,}} {{nowrap|'''76'''\u20131 ('''71'''),}} {{nowrap|'''134'''\u20134 ('''54''', '''70'''),}} {{nowrap|34\u201388 (88),}} {{nowrap|0\u2013119 (111),}} {{nowrap|47\u201374,}} {{nowrap|'''132'''\u20130 ('''131'''),}} {{nowrap|'''80'''\u201319 ('''75''')}}\n| Session 4<br/>{{nowrap|Session score: ('''5'''\u20134), Match score '''18'''\u201315}}\n| {{nowrap|72\u201322,}} {{nowrap|36\u2013'''74''',}} {{nowrap|76\u20131 (71),}} {{nowrap|134\u20134 (54, 70),}} {{nowrap|34\u2013'''88''' ('''88'''),}} {{nowrap|0\u2013'''119''' ('''111'''),}} {{nowrap|47\u2013'''74''',}} {{nowrap|132\u20130 (131),}} {{nowrap|80\u201319 (75)}}\n|\n| 131\n| Highest break\n| '''141'''\n| 2\n| Century breaks\n| 2\n| '''14'''\n| 50+ breaks\n| 8\n| {{flagicon|ENG}} '''Mark Selby''' wins the 2017 Betfred World Snooker Championship.\n<!-- Frame header info -->\n|Best of 19 frames\n|Best of 25 frames\n|Best of 25 frames\n|Best of 33 frames\n}}\n\n==Qualifying==\nQualifying for the 2017 World Snooker Championship took place from 5 to 12 April 2017, at the Ponds Forge International Sports Centre in Sheffield.<ref name=\"yeKsC\" /> There were 128 competitors who took part in the three qualifying rounds, with the 16 winners of the third round matches progressing to the main stage of the tournament at the Crucible Theatre, also in Sheffield.<ref name=\"criteria\" /> All qualifying matches were played as best-of-19-frames.<ref name=\"criteria\" /> The 128 players that entered the qualifying competition included tour players ranked outside the top 16, and 16 amateur players, all of whom achieved success through the WPBSA qualifying criteria.<ref name=\"criteria\" /> The following amateur players were invited to compete:<ref name=\"criteria\" /><ref name=\"yeKsC\" />\n* Home Nations NGB qualifiers:  [[Jackson Page]], [[Tyler Rees]], [[Ross Vallance]], [[Chris Totten]],  [[Jordan Brown (snooker player)|Jordan Brown]],  [[Patrick Wallace]],  [[Jamie Bodle]],  [[Wayne Townsend (snooker player)|Wayne Townsend]]\n* [[2016 IBSF World Under-21 Snooker Championship]] winner: [[Xu Si]]\n* [[2017 EBSA European Snooker Championship]] runner-up: [[Andres Petrov]] (tournament won by Chris Totten, who had already qualified)\n* [[2017 EBSA European Under-21 Snooker Championship]] winner: [[Alexander Ursenbacher]]\n* EBSA Order of Merit 2016/17: [[Gerard Greene]], [[Zack Richardson]]\n* [[2017 World Seniors Championship]] winner: [[Peter Lines]]\n* [[Ladies World Snooker Championship|2016 WLBS World Women's Championship]] winner: [[Reanne Evans]]\n* [[Ladies World Snooker Championship|2017 WLBS World Women's Championship]] winner: [[Ng On-yee]]\n\nThe winner of the [[2016 IBSF World Snooker Championship \u2013 Men's|2016 IBSF World Snooker Championship]], [[Soheil Vahedi]] of Iran, was also invited but could not obtain a visa in time to compete.<ref name=\"criteria\" /> Two amateur players, England's [[Andy Hicks]] and Poland's [[Adam Stefan\u00f3w]], were invited to replace the absent professional players [[Jamie Burnett]] and [[Rouzi Maimaiti]].<ref name=\"4qUN7\" /> Hicks and Stefan\u00f3w were selected from the 2016 [[Q School (snooker)|Q School]] Order of Merit, as the top-ranked players that had not already qualified for the tournament.<ref name=\"cNpM0\" />\n\n===Round 1===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{|class=\"wikitable \" \n|-\n!width=200|Player\n!width=60|Score\n!width=200|Player\n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Mark Williams (snooker player)|Mark Williams]]|WAL}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20137 || {{flagathlete|[[Zhao Xintong]]|CHN}}\n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Liam Highfield]]|ENG}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20132 || {{flagathlete|[[Andres Petrov]]|EST}}\n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Stuart Carrington]]|ENG}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20132 || {{flagathlete|[[Alex Borg]]|MLT}}\n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Andrew Higginson]]|ENG}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20138 || {{flagathlete|[[Michael Georgiou]]|CYP}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:lightgrey\" | \n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Tom Ford (snooker player)|Tom Ford]]|ENG}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20132 || {{flagathlete|[[Jamie Bodle]]|ENG}}\n|-\n| '''{{flagathlete|[[Chris Wakelin]]|ENG}}''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''10'''\u20135 || {{flagathlete|[[Elliot Slessor]]|ENG}}\n